<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3072] Client should be interruptible; APIs should all change to let out Interrupted Exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3072</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue comes of discussion over in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3064&quot; title=&quot;Long sleeping in HConnectionManager after thread is interrupted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3064&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3064&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  That issue hacks in some basic interruptibility.  We should revamp client so all APIs can be interrupted/throw IE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
