                            <comment id="14064296" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 16 Jul 2014 23:05:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What would you like to do with this issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14064539" author="stack" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2014 03:35:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Too inspecific.  Resolving later.  No work done on it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14068358" author="nkeywal" created="Mon, 21 Jul 2014 09:48:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fwiw, some work has been done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10337&quot; title=&quot;HTable.get() uninteruptible&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10337&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-10337&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and others.&lt;br/&gt;
The strategy to limit the impact on the interface was to use InterruptedIOException. There is a test for get (TestClientOperationInterrupt), so if it breaks we will see it. Not all paths (puts...) are covered however.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
